{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":835,"text":"I love a great mystery,"},{"time":2901,"text":"and I'm fascinated by the greatest\nunsolved mystery in science,"},{"time":7313,"text":"perhaps because it's personal."},{"time":9681,"text":"It's about who we are,"},{"time":11539,"text":"and I can't help but be curious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14186,"text":"The mystery is this:"},{"time":16275,"text":"What is the relationship\nbetween your brain"},{"time":19710,"text":"and your conscious experiences,"},{"time":21221,"text":"such as your experience\nof the taste of chocolate"},{"time":23891,"text":"or the feeling of velvet?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":26805,"text":"Now, this mystery is not new."},{"time":28999,"text":"In 1868, Thomas Huxley wrote,"},{"time":32598,"text":"\"How it is that anything so remarkable\nas a state of consciousness comes about"},{"time":37892,"text":"as the result of irritating nervous tissue"},{"time":41259,"text":"is just as unaccountable"},{"time":43325,"text":"as the appearance of the genie\nwhen Aladdin rubbed his lamp.\""},{"time":49268,"text":"Now, Huxley knew that brain activity"},{"time":51545,"text":"and conscious experiences are correlated,"},{"time":54819,"text":"but he didn't know why."},{"time":56978,"text":"To the science of his day,\nit was a mystery."},{"time":60299,"text":"In the years since Huxley,"},{"time":62435,"text":"science has learned a lot\nabout brain activity,"},{"time":65801,"text":"but the relationship\nbetween brain activity"},{"time":67822,"text":"and conscious experiences\nis still a mystery."},{"time":70910,"text":"Why? Why have we made so little progress?"},{"time":74555,"text":"Well, some experts think\nthat we can't solve this problem"},{"time":79414,"text":"because we lack the necessary\nconcepts and intelligence."},{"time":83883,"text":"We don't expect monkeys to solve\nproblems in quantum mechanics,"},{"time":87952,"text":"and as it happens, we can't expect\nour species to solve this problem either."},{"time":92527,"text":"Well, I disagree. I'm more optimistic."},{"time":95661,"text":"I think we've simply\nmade a false assumption."},{"time":98703,"text":"Once we fix it, we just\nmight solve this problem."},{"time":102209,"text":"Today, I'd like tell you\nwhat that assumption is,"},{"time":104626,"text":"why it's false, and how to fix it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107874,"text":"Let's begin with a question:"},{"time":109778,"text":"Do we see reality as it is?"},{"time":112866,"text":"I open my eyes"},{"time":114561,"text":"and I have an experience that I describe\nas a red tomato a meter away."},{"time":120606,"text":"As a result, I come to believe\nthat in reality,"},{"time":123849,"text":"there's a red tomato a meter away."},{"time":126751,"text":"I then close my eyes, and my experience\nchanges to a gray field,"},{"time":132425,"text":"but is it still the case that in reality,\nthere's a red tomato a meter away?"},{"time":138361,"text":"I think so, but could I be wrong?"},{"time":141913,"text":"Could I be misinterpreting\nthe nature of my perceptions?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":147351,"text":"We have misinterpreted\nour perceptions before."},{"time":150551,"text":"We used to think the Earth is flat,\nbecause it looks that way."},{"time":154707,"text":"Pythagorus discovered that we were wrong."},{"time":157586,"text":"Then we thought that the Earth\nis the unmoving center of the Universe,"},{"time":161603,"text":"again because it looks that way."},{"time":164406,"text":"Copernicus and Galileo discovered,\nagain, that we were wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169312,"text":"Galileo then wondered if we might\nbe misinterpreting our experiences"},{"time":173400,"text":"in other ways."},{"time":174908,"text":"He wrote: \"I think that tastes,\nodors, colors, and so on"},{"time":179917,"text":"reside in consciousness."},{"time":182291,"text":"Hence if the living creature were removed,\nall these qualities would be annihilated.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":188955,"text":"Now, that's a stunning claim."},{"time":191184,"text":"Could Galileo be right?"},{"time":192995,"text":"Could we really be misinterpreting\nour experiences that badly?"},{"time":197593,"text":"What does modern science\nhave to say about this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":200704,"text":"Well, neuroscientists tell us\nthat about a third of the brain's cortex"},{"time":205928,"text":"is engaged in vision."},{"time":207786,"text":"When you simply open your eyes\nand look about this room,"},{"time":211292,"text":"billions of neurons\nand trillions of synapses are engaged."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215564,"text":"Now, this is a bit surprising,"},{"time":217172,"text":"because to the extent that\nwe think about vision at all,"},{"time":219813,"text":"we think of it as like a camera."},{"time":222650,"text":"It just takes a picture\nof objective reality as it is."},{"time":226590,"text":"Now, there is a part of vision\nthat's like a camera:"},{"time":230290,"text":"the eye has a lens that focuses\nan image on the back of the eye"},{"time":234929,"text":"where there are 130 million\nphotoreceptors,"},{"time":238319,"text":"so the eye is like a 130-megapixel camera."},{"time":242219,"text":"But that doesn't explain\nthe billions of neurons"},{"time":245702,"text":"and trillions of synapses\nthat are engaged in vision."},{"time":249324,"text":"What are these neurons up to?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":251623,"text":"Well, neuroscientists tell us\nthat they are creating, in real time,"},{"time":255830,"text":"all the shapes, objects, colors,\nand motions that we see."},{"time":260160,"text":"It feels like we're just taking a snapshot\nof this room the way it is,"},{"time":263651,"text":"but in fact, we're constructing\neverything that we see."},{"time":267226,"text":"We don't construct\nthe whole world at once."},{"time":270407,"text":"We construct what we need in the moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273542,"text":"Now, there are many demonstrations\nthat are quite compelling"},{"time":276909,"text":"that we construct what we see."},{"time":278720,"text":"I'll just show you two."},{"time":280763,"text":"In this example, you see some red discs\nwith bits cut out of them,"},{"time":286529,"text":"but if I just rotate\nthe disks a little bit,"},{"time":289470,"text":"suddenly, you see a 3D cube\npop out of the screen."},{"time":294207,"text":"Now, the screen of course is flat,"},{"time":297040,"text":"so the three-dimensional cube\nthat you're experiencing"},{"time":299640,"text":"must be your construction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303397,"text":"In this next example,"},{"time":305310,"text":"you see glowing blue bars\nwith pretty sharp edges"},{"time":309534,"text":"moving across a field of dots."},{"time":313708,"text":"In fact, no dots move."},{"time":316845,"text":"All I'm doing from frame to frame\nis changing the colors of dots"},{"time":321466,"text":"from blue to black or black to blue."},{"time":323927,"text":"But when I do this quickly,"},{"time":325761,"text":"your visual system creates\nthe glowing blue bars"},{"time":329476,"text":"with the sharp edges and the motion."},{"time":332147,"text":"There are many more examples,\nbut these are just two"},{"time":334817,"text":"that you construct what you see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337580,"text":"But neuroscientists go further."},{"time":341395,"text":"They say that we reconstruct reality."},{"time":346496,"text":"So, when I have an experience\nthat I describe as a red tomato,"},{"time":350722,"text":"that experience is actually\nan accurate reconstruction"},{"time":354855,"text":"of the properties of a real red tomato"},{"time":356970,"text":"that would exist\neven if I weren't looking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361595,"text":"Now, why would neuroscientists\nsay that we don't just construct,"},{"time":364816,"text":"we reconstruct?"},{"time":366696,"text":"Well, the standard argument given"},{"time":369227,"text":"is usually an evolutionary one."},{"time":372941,"text":"Those of our ancestors\nwho saw more accurately"},{"time":375380,"text":"had a competitive advantage compared\nto those who saw less accurately,"},{"time":380233,"text":"and therefore they were more likely\nto pass on their genes."},{"time":382989,"text":"We are the offspring of those\nwho saw more accurately,"},{"time":386380,"text":"and so we can be confident that,\nin the normal case,"},{"time":389149,"text":"our perceptions are accurate."},{"time":391680,"text":"You see this in the standard textbooks."},{"time":395375,"text":"One textbook says, for example,"},{"time":397369,"text":"\"Evolutionarily speaking,"},{"time":399340,"text":"vision is useful precisely\nbecause it is so accurate.\""},{"time":403383,"text":"So the idea is that accurate perceptions\nare fitter perceptions."},{"time":408181,"text":"They give you a survival advantage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410325,"text":"Now, is this correct?"},{"time":412240,"text":"Is this the right interpretation\nof evolutionary theory?"},{"time":414899,"text":"Well, let's first look at a couple\nof examples in nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418800,"text":"The Australian jewel beetle"},{"time":421238,"text":"is dimpled, glossy and brown."},{"time":424349,"text":"The female is flightless."},{"time":426694,"text":"The male flies, looking,\nof course, for a hot female."},{"time":430711,"text":"When he finds one, he alights and mates."},{"time":434659,"text":"There's another species in the outback,"},{"time":437130,"text":"Homo sapiens."},{"time":438464,"text":"The male of this species\nhas a massive brain"},{"time":441531,"text":"that he uses to hunt for cold beer."},{"time":445889,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":447168,"text":"And when he finds one, he drains it,"},{"time":449542,"text":"and sometimes throws the bottle\ninto the outback."},{"time":452932,"text":"Now, as it happens, these bottles\nare dimpled, glossy,"},{"time":457180,"text":"and just the right shade of brown\nto tickle the fancy of these beetles."},{"time":462772,"text":"The males swarm all over\nthe bottles trying to mate."},{"time":467582,"text":"They lose all interest\nin the real females."},{"time":470369,"text":"Classic case of the male\nleaving the female for the bottle."},{"time":474572,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":479402,"text":"The species almost went extinct."},{"time":482443,"text":"Australia had to change its bottles\nto save its beetles."},{"time":486752,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":489752,"text":"Now, the males had successfully\nfound females for thousands,"},{"time":493960,"text":"perhaps millions of years."},{"time":496398,"text":"It looked like they saw reality\nas it is, but apparently not."},{"time":500832,"text":"Evolution had given them a hack."},{"time":503689,"text":"A female is anything dimpled,\nglossy and brown,"},{"time":508425,"text":"the bigger the better."},{"time":510701,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":512535,"text":"Even when crawling all over the bottle,\nthe male couldn't discover his mistake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517945,"text":"Now, you might say, beetles, sure,\nthey're very simple creatures,"},{"time":521590,"text":"but surely not mammals."},{"time":523448,"text":"Mammals don't rely on tricks."},{"time":526165,"text":"Well, I won't dwell on this,\nbut you get the idea. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532178,"text":"So this raises an important\ntechnical question:"},{"time":535336,"text":"Does natural selection really favor\nseeing reality as it is?"},{"time":541877,"text":"Fortunately, we don't have\nto wave our hands and guess;"},{"time":545413,"text":"evolution is a mathematically\nprecise theory."},{"time":548594,"text":"We can use the equations of evolution\nto check this out."},{"time":552147,"text":"We can have various organisms\nin artificial worlds compete"},{"time":556300,"text":"and see which survive and which thrive,"},{"time":558253,"text":"which sensory systems are more fit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561806,"text":"A key notion in those\nequations is fitness."},{"time":565891,"text":"Consider this steak:"},{"time":569956,"text":"What does this steak do\nfor the fitness of an animal?"},{"time":573438,"text":"Well, for a hungry lion looking to eat,\nit enhances fitness."},{"time":580179,"text":"For a well-fed lion looking to mate,\nit doesn't enhance fitness."},{"time":586053,"text":"And for a rabbit in any state,\nit doesn't enhance fitness,"},{"time":589924,"text":"so fitness does depend\non reality as it is, yes,"},{"time":594048,"text":"but also on the organism,\nits state and its action."},{"time":598236,"text":"Fitness is not the same thing\nas reality as it is,"},{"time":601789,"text":"and it's fitness,\nand not reality as it is,"},{"time":605272,"text":"that figures centrally\nin the equations of evolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609451,"text":"So, in my lab,"},{"time":612642,"text":"we have run hundreds of thousands\nof evolutionary game simulations"},{"time":616417,"text":"with lots of different\nrandomly chosen worlds"},{"time":619482,"text":"and organisms that compete\nfor resources in those worlds."},{"time":623661,"text":"Some of the organisms\nsee all of the reality,"},{"time":627980,"text":"others see just part of the reality,"},{"time":629869,"text":"and some see none of the reality,"},{"time":631974,"text":"only fitness."},{"time":634240,"text":"Who wins?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":636290,"text":"Well, I hate to break it to you,\nbut perception of reality goes extinct."},{"time":642255,"text":"In almost every simulation,"},{"time":644164,"text":"organisms that see none of reality"},{"time":646346,"text":"but are just tuned to fitness"},{"time":648436,"text":"drive to extinction all the organisms\nthat perceive reality as it is."},{"time":653660,"text":"So the bottom line is, evolution\ndoes not favor veridical,"},{"time":658250,"text":"or accurate perceptions."},{"time":659906,"text":"Those perceptions of reality go extinct."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663668,"text":"Now, this is a bit stunning."},{"time":665688,"text":"How can it be that not seeing\nthe world accurately"},{"time":669370,"text":"gives us a survival advantage?"},{"time":671190,"text":"That is a bit counterintuitive."},{"time":673303,"text":"But remember the jewel beetle."},{"time":675138,"text":"The jewel beetle survived\nfor thousands, perhaps millions of years,"},{"time":678899,"text":"using simple tricks and hacks."},{"time":681593,"text":"What the equations\nof evolution are telling us"},{"time":684770,"text":"is that all organisms, including us, \nare in the same boat as the jewel beetle."},{"time":690413,"text":"We do not see reality as it is."},{"time":692343,"text":"We're shaped with tricks\nand hacks that keep us alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696615,"text":"Still,"},{"time":698635,"text":"we need some help with our intuitions."},{"time":700702,"text":"How can not perceiving\nreality as it is be useful?"},{"time":705485,"text":"Well, fortunately, we have\na very helpful metaphor:"},{"time":709154,"text":"the desktop interface on your computer."},{"time":711986,"text":"Consider that blue icon\nfor a TED Talk that you're writing."},{"time":716119,"text":"Now, the icon is blue and rectangular"},{"time":720123,"text":"and in the lower right corner\nof the desktop."},{"time":723324,"text":"Does that mean that the text file itself\nin the computer is blue,"},{"time":728200,"text":"rectangular, and in the lower\nright-hand corner of the computer?"},{"time":731955,"text":"Of course not."},{"time":733278,"text":"Anyone who thought that misinterprets\nthe purpose of the interface."},{"time":737987,"text":"It's not there to show you\nthe reality of the computer."},{"time":740755,"text":"In fact, it's there to hide that reality."},{"time":743680,"text":"You don't want to know about the diodes"},{"time":745555,"text":"and resistors and all\nthe megabytes of software."},{"time":747805,"text":"If you had to deal with that,\nyou could never write your text file"},{"time":750936,"text":"or edit your photo."},{"time":752411,"text":"So the idea is that evolution\nhas given us an interface"},{"time":757128,"text":"that hides reality and guides\nadaptive behavior."},{"time":761443,"text":"Space and time, as you\nperceive them right now,"},{"time":764461,"text":"are your desktop."},{"time":766635,"text":"Physical objects are simply icons\nin that desktop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772192,"text":"There's an obvious objection."},{"time":774413,"text":"Hoffman, if you think that train\ncoming down the track at 200 MPH"},{"time":778361,"text":"is just an icon of your desktop,"},{"time":780822,"text":"why don't you step in front of it?"},{"time":782947,"text":"And after you're gone,\nand your theory with you,"},{"time":785240,"text":"we'll know that there's more\nto that train than just an icon."},{"time":788554,"text":"Well, I wouldn't step\nin front of that train"},{"time":790597,"text":"for the same reason"},{"time":792153,"text":"that I wouldn't carelessly drag\nthat icon to the trash can:"},{"time":796448,"text":"not because I take the icon literally --"},{"time":799629,"text":"the file is not literally blue\nor rectangular --"},{"time":802934,"text":"but I do take it seriously."},{"time":805260,"text":"I could lose weeks of work."},{"time":807291,"text":"Similarly, evolution has shaped us"},{"time":809845,"text":"with perceptual symbols\nthat are designed to keep us alive."},{"time":814811,"text":"We'd better take them seriously."},{"time":817276,"text":"If you see a snake, don't pick it up."},{"time":820391,"text":"If you see a cliff, don't jump off."},{"time":823150,"text":"They're designed to keep us safe,\nand we should take them seriously."},{"time":826726,"text":"That does not mean that we\nshould take them literally."},{"time":829417,"text":"That's a logical error."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831671,"text":"Another objection: There's\nnothing really new here."},{"time":834876,"text":"Physicists have told us for a long time\nthat the metal of that train looks solid"},{"time":838800,"text":"but really it's mostly empty space\nwith microscopic particles zipping around."},{"time":843188,"text":"There's nothing new here."},{"time":844676,"text":"Well, not exactly."},{"time":846880,"text":"It's like saying, I know that\nthat blue icon on the desktop"},{"time":850920,"text":"is not the reality of the computer,"},{"time":853219,"text":"but if I pull out my trusty\nmagnifying glass and look really closely,"},{"time":856678,"text":"I see little pixels,"},{"time":858489,"text":"and that's the reality of the computer."},{"time":860950,"text":"Well, not really -- you're still\non the desktop, and that's the point."},{"time":864758,"text":"Those microscopic particles\nare still in space and time:"},{"time":867754,"text":"they're still in the user interface."},{"time":870145,"text":"So I'm saying something far more radical\nthan those physicists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874727,"text":"Finally, you might object,"},{"time":876200,"text":"look, we all see the train,"},{"time":878759,"text":"therefore none of us constructs the train."},{"time":881801,"text":"But remember this example."},{"time":883891,"text":"In this example, we all see a cube,"},{"time":887597,"text":"but the screen is flat,"},{"time":889690,"text":"so the cube that you see\nis the cube that you construct."},{"time":893736,"text":"We all see a cube"},{"time":895779,"text":"because we all, each one of us,\nconstructs the cube that we see."},{"time":900638,"text":"The same is true of the train."},{"time":902698,"text":"We all see a train because\nwe each see the train that we construct,"},{"time":907180,"text":"and the same is true\nof all physical objects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912343,"text":"We're inclined to think that perception\nis like a window on reality as it is."},{"time":917396,"text":"The theory of evolution is telling us\nthat this is an incorrect interpretation"},{"time":922400,"text":"of our perceptions."},{"time":925095,"text":"Instead, reality is more like a 3D desktop"},{"time":928639,"text":"that's designed to hide\nthe complexity of the real world"},{"time":931936,"text":"and guide adaptive behavior."},{"time":934282,"text":"Space as you perceive it is your desktop."},{"time":937210,"text":"Physical objects are just\nthe icons in that desktop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941456,"text":"We used to think that the Earth is flat\nbecause it looks that way."},{"time":945520,"text":"Then we thought that the Earth\nis the unmoving center of reality"},{"time":948654,"text":"because it looks that way."},{"time":950378,"text":"We were wrong."},{"time":951520,"text":"We had misinterpreted our perceptions."},{"time":954910,"text":"Now we believe that spacetime and objects"},{"time":958319,"text":"are the nature of reality as it is."},{"time":961453,"text":"The theory of evolution is telling us\nthat once again, we're wrong."},{"time":965377,"text":"We're misinterpreting the content\nof our perceptual experiences."},{"time":970416,"text":"There's something that exists\nwhen you don't look,"},{"time":972947,"text":"but it's not spacetime\nand physical objects."},{"time":976350,"text":"It's as hard for us to let go\nof spacetime and objects"},{"time":979378,"text":"as it is for the jewel beetle\nto let go of its bottle."},{"time":982861,"text":"Why? Because we're blind\nto our own blindnesses."},{"time":988409,"text":"But we have an advantage\nover the jewel beetle:"},{"time":990756,"text":"our science and technology."},{"time":992544,"text":"By peering through the lens of a telescope"},{"time":994935,"text":"we discovered that the Earth\nis not the unmoving center of reality,"},{"time":999571,"text":"and by peering through the lens\nof the theory of evolution"},{"time":1002449,"text":"we discovered that spacetime and objects"},{"time":1004771,"text":"are not the nature of reality."},{"time":1007139,"text":"When I have a perceptual experience\nthat I describe as a red tomato,"},{"time":1011424,"text":"I am interacting with reality,"},{"time":1014361,"text":"but that reality is not a red tomato\nand is nothing like a red tomato."},{"time":1019571,"text":"Similarly, when I have an experience\nthat I describe as a lion or a steak,"},{"time":1024972,"text":"I'm interacting with reality,"},{"time":1026820,"text":"but that reality is not a lion or a steak."},{"time":1029978,"text":"And here's the kicker:"},{"time":1031998,"text":"When I have a perceptual experience\nthat I describe as a brain, or neurons,"},{"time":1036688,"text":"I am interacting with reality,"},{"time":1038778,"text":"but that reality is not a brain or neurons"},{"time":1042307,"text":"and is nothing like a brain or neurons."},{"time":1045805,"text":"And that reality, whatever it is,"},{"time":1050584,"text":"is the real source of cause and effect"},{"time":1054195,"text":"in the world -- not brains, not neurons."},{"time":1058227,"text":"Brains and neurons\nhave no causal powers."},{"time":1060827,"text":"They cause none of our\nperceptual experiences,"},{"time":1063428,"text":"and none of our behavior."},{"time":1065216,"text":"Brains and neurons are a species-specific\nset of symbols, a hack."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1070592,"text":"What does this mean\nfor the mystery of consciousness?"},{"time":1073923,"text":"Well, it opens up new possibilities."},{"time":1077916,"text":"For instance,"},{"time":1079611,"text":"perhaps reality is some vast machine\nthat causes our conscious experiences."},{"time":1086590,"text":"I doubt this, but it's worth exploring."},{"time":1090260,"text":"Perhaps reality is some vast,\ninteracting network of conscious agents,"},{"time":1095609,"text":"simple and complex, that cause\neach other's conscious experiences."},{"time":1101182,"text":"Actually, this isn't as crazy\nan idea as it seems,"},{"time":1104432,"text":"and I'm currently exploring it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1106592,"text":"But here's the point:"},{"time":1108658,"text":"Once we let go of our massively intuitive"},{"time":1111979,"text":"but massively false assumption\nabout the nature of reality,"},{"time":1115903,"text":"it opens up new ways to think\nabout life's greatest mystery."},{"time":1121251,"text":"I bet that reality will end up\nturning out to be more fascinating"},{"time":1125860,"text":"and unexpected than we've ever imagined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1129834,"text":"The theory of evolution presents us\nwith the ultimate dare:"},{"time":1134222,"text":"Dare to recognize that perception\nis not about seeing truth,"},{"time":1139364,"text":"it's about having kids."},{"time":1143460,"text":"And by the way, even this TED\nis just in your head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1148200,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1150244,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1160786,"text":"Chris Anderson: If that's\nreally you there, thank you."},{"time":1164221,"text":"So there's so much from this."},{"time":1167152,"text":"I mean, first of all, some people\nmay just be profoundly depressed"},{"time":1170421,"text":"at the thought that,\nif evolution does not favor reality,"},{"time":1175970,"text":"I mean, doesn't that to some extent\nundermine all our endeavors here,"},{"time":1179300,"text":"all our ability to think\nthat we can think the truth,"},{"time":1181984,"text":"possibly even including\nyour own theory, if you go there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1185490,"text":"Donald Hoffman: Well, this does not\nstop us from a successful science."},{"time":1189944,"text":"What we have is one theory\nthat turned out to be false,"},{"time":1192756,"text":"that perception is like reality\nand reality is like our perceptions."},{"time":1197215,"text":"That theory turns out to be false."},{"time":1198900,"text":"Okay, throw that theory away."},{"time":1200318,"text":"That doesn't stop us from now postulating\nall sorts of other theories"},{"time":1203572,"text":"about the nature of reality,"},{"time":1204930,"text":"so it's actually progress to recognize\nthat one of our theories was false."},{"time":1208535,"text":"So science continues as normal.\nThere's no problem here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1211193,"text":"CA: So you think it's possible\n-- (Laughter) --"},{"time":1213794,"text":"This is cool, but what you're saying\nI think is it's possible that evolution"},{"time":1217904,"text":"can still get you to reason."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1220551,"text":"DH: Yes. Now that's a very,\nvery good point."},{"time":1222864,"text":"The evolutionary game simulations that I\nshowed were specifically about perception,"},{"time":1227391,"text":"and they do show that our perceptions\nhave been shaped"},{"time":1229969,"text":"not to show us reality as it is,"},{"time":1231849,"text":"but that does not mean the same thing\nabout our logic or mathematics."},{"time":1236122,"text":"We haven't done these simulations,\nbut my bet is that we'll find"},{"time":1239744,"text":"that there are some selection pressures\nfor our logic and our mathematics"},{"time":1243366,"text":"to be at least in the direction of truth."},{"time":1245572,"text":"I mean, if you're like me,\nmath and logic is not easy."},{"time":1248219,"text":"We don't get it all right, but at least\nthe selection pressures are not"},{"time":1251570,"text":"uniformly away from true math and logic."},{"time":1253908,"text":"So I think that we'll find that we have\nto look at each cognitive faculty"},{"time":1257228,"text":"one at a time and see\nwhat evolution does to it."},{"time":1259852,"text":"What's true about perception may not\nbe true about math and logic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1263613,"text":"CA: I mean, really what you're proposing\nis a kind of modern-day Bishop Berkeley"},{"time":1267607,"text":"interpretation of the world:"},{"time":1269998,"text":"consciousness causes matter,\nnot the other way around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1272947,"text":"DH: Well, it's slightly\ndifferent than Berkeley."},{"time":1275339,"text":"Berkeley thought that, he was a deist,\nand he thought that the ultimate"},{"time":1278701,"text":"nature of reality is God\nand so forth,"},{"time":1280740,"text":"and I don't need to go\nwhere Berkeley's going,"},{"time":1283850,"text":"so it's quite a bit\ndifferent from Berkeley."},{"time":1287725,"text":"I call this conscious realism.\nIt's actually a very different approach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1291235,"text":"CA: Don, I could literally talk with you\nfor hours, and I hope to do that.\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1294825,"text":"Thanks so much for that.\nDH: Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}